With that in mind, I was considering replacing it. I want the Bus to be
functional, AND original looking, but I don't mind so much about changing
things "under the hood" since the Bus doesn't have the original motor
anyway.

That said, is it required that I have a specific diameter of line going from
the carburetor to the brake booster?

Or can I use.. say a large steel fuel line most of the way?
